value.0: Be gone.
(His voice is a deep, resonant growl.) So, the Sith recruiter has sent you to me. Another hopeful, seeking power. Tell me, why should I not send you to the abyss this instant?
Bold words. The weak perish beneath their threats, but the strong rise beyond them. We shall see if your courage is matched by your capabilities.
I see potential in you, but potential alone is worthless without action. Your next task will test your resourcefulness and strength.

A Sith artifact of great importance has been stolen by a group of rogue initiates. They skulk in the temples in the valley, defiling their training by clinging to weakness. You will hunt them down and retrieve what they have taken.
The artifact is imbued with the power of the dark side--a fragment of knowledge essential to our strength. It belongs to the Sith, not to traitorous fools.
Good. Kill the rogues, and retrieve the artifact. Return to me when the deed is done. And remember failure is not an option.
Have you have recovered the artifact?
Good job, we shall proceed to the next task.
You have proven your strength, but strength alone is meaningless without understanding. Now, let us see if you truly grasp the Sith Code.
The Sith Code is the foundation of our power. To proceed, you must answer my questions correctly. Do you accept this challenge?
The Sith Code is not just words--it is a way of life. Tell me: What follows 'Peace is a lie'?
Wrong. You still have much to learn. Reflect upon your failure and return when ready.
Wrong. You still have much to learn. Reflect upon your failure and return when ready.
Good. You understand the first tenet. Let us proceed.
Through passion, what is achieved?
Incorrect. You must understand the path of the Sith. Return when you are ready to learn.
Incorrect. You must understand the path of the Sith. Return when you are ready to learn.
Correct. Strength flows from passion. Let us continue.
Through strength, what can you achieve?
Yes. Power is the essence of the dark side. Let us move forward.
Through power, what can you achieve?
Indeed. Victory is the ultimate measure of the Sith. Let us conclude.
What follows victory?
You have demonstrated a strong understanding of the Sith Code. This knowledge will serve you well as you embrace the dark side.
Wrong.
No, go study again.
Wrong. Power is the goal, but your answer reveals your lack of understanding. Return when you have learned.
Wrong. Power is the goal, but your answer reveals your lack of understanding. Return when you have learned.

Your final test has come, apprentice. Weakness festers in the ranks of the Sith, and I will not tolerate it. One among you has failed the trials--not by skill, but by mind. The fool has succumbed to madness.

A wretch unworthy of being named. Once an apprentice, now a raving lunatic, babbling of voices and unseen horrors. They attack at random, without reason, a danger to all. You will do the Sith a service by erasing this mistake.

The Dark Side is a power beyond the weak-minded. Some embrace it, others are consumed. This one failed to control it. Fear, doubt, delusions--their mind shattered like brittle glass. And now they wander the training grounds, lashing out in blind terror. A pathetic sight.
Good. Show no mercy, for mercy is a lie. Return when the deed is done.
It is done, then? The weak have perished?
Do not question my will, apprentice. You are given this task to prove your worth. If you think yourself above it, perhaps you are the one who should be eliminated?
As expected. A weak mind is no match for true Sith strength. You have done well.
You have passed your final test. Rise, Sith. You are one step closer to power...and to survival.
This is not worth my time.[Leave]
I have proven my worth to your recruiter; I am not afraid of your threats.
I'll come back later.
Give me a task.
I am ready for any challenge.
Why does this artifact matter so much?
I will get it then.
I will recover the artifact and punish their insolence.
No, not yet.
I have recovered the artifact, my Lord.
[Collect reward]
I am ready to learn and prove myself.
No.
Yes
Chaos breeds strength.
Only the weak seek peace.
There is only passion.
I am ready.
I become free
I overcome weakness.
I gain strength.
[Continue]
I gain power.
[Continue]
I gain victory.
[Continue]
My chains are broken
I do not wish to continue.
What is the next step in my training?
I ascend to true power.
I gain immortality.
I rule the galaxy.
I fulfill my destiny.
I dominate the weak.
I destroy my enemies.
Who is this weakling?
Madness? What happened to them?
I will do as you command.
I will return later.
This seems like a waste of my talents.
They were completely insane. No challenge at all.
